00:00:10.090 --> 00:00:11.690
JONATHAN BERI: Hi, and welcome
to this week's Google

00:00:11.690 --> 00:00:12.910
Developers Live.

00:00:12.910 --> 00:00:14.070
My name is Jonathan Beri.

00:00:14.070 --> 00:00:16.040
I'm a developer advocate
for Google+.

00:00:16.040 --> 00:00:17.090
And with me is--

00:00:17.090 --> 00:00:18.630
JOANNA SMITH: I'm Joanna Smith,
and I'm a developer

00:00:18.630 --> 00:00:19.550
programs engineer.

00:00:19.550 --> 00:00:21.710
And I'm really happy to be
kicking off 2013 Google+

00:00:21.710 --> 00:00:23.320
Developers Live.

00:00:23.320 --> 00:00:23.710
JONATHAN BERI: Awesome.

00:00:23.710 --> 00:00:24.290
Yes it is.

00:00:24.290 --> 00:00:26.410
It's also a kickoff up for
our new platform--

00:00:26.410 --> 00:00:29.610
the next generation of the
Google+ Platform, and a major

00:00:29.610 --> 00:00:30.780
leap for developers.

00:00:30.780 --> 00:00:34.320
Today we introduce Google+
Sign-in, which is a simple and

00:00:34.320 --> 00:00:37.530
secure way for users to sign
into your apps, both on the

00:00:37.530 --> 00:00:39.750
web and in mobile.

00:00:39.750 --> 00:00:42.060
Leveraging the power of Google+,
integrating it deeply

00:00:42.060 --> 00:00:44.960
applications, as well as some
other magic that we are

00:00:44.960 --> 00:00:46.300
introducing with this release.

00:00:46.300 --> 00:00:47.520
So we're super excited
about it.

00:00:47.520 --> 00:00:49.570
JOANNA SMITH: It's
really cool.

00:00:49.570 --> 00:00:52.710
And to show you guys-- so you
can visualize how this is

00:00:52.710 --> 00:00:55.200
going to look-- we actually have
a demo that we wanted to

00:00:55.200 --> 00:00:57.550
show you to kick off
today's episode.

00:00:57.550 --> 00:01:01.160
And the most important thing
to notice as we go to our

00:01:01.160 --> 00:01:04.319
website is the shiny,
red button.

00:01:04.319 --> 00:01:07.535
We're very proud of our Sign-in
with Google button.

00:01:07.535 --> 00:01:08.785
JONATHAN BERI: So we have
a quick link here.

00:01:13.210 --> 00:01:16.210
JOANNA SMITH: And so
when you go to--

00:01:16.210 --> 00:01:19.810
as a developer, you can offer
this button in your app, on

00:01:19.810 --> 00:01:22.470
mobile-- iOS, or Android--
or on your website.

00:01:22.470 --> 00:01:25.180
And any user can just come to
your site like normal, see the

00:01:25.180 --> 00:01:27.720
button, and decide to connect
their profile, which will open

00:01:27.720 --> 00:01:29.960
an authentication dialog where
they can enter their

00:01:29.960 --> 00:01:30.480
credentials.

00:01:30.480 --> 00:01:33.360
Or if they're already logged
in to Google, they can just

00:01:33.360 --> 00:01:35.180
continue with the
authorization.

00:01:35.180 --> 00:01:37.550
What's really great about this
dialogue, though, is it makes

00:01:37.550 --> 00:01:39.680
it very clear for the user
to see how they can

00:01:39.680 --> 00:01:41.300
control their privacy.

00:01:41.300 --> 00:01:42.420
JONATHAN BERI: So I have
this dialogue open.

00:01:42.420 --> 00:01:44.780
Why don't you walk us through
what we're seeing right now?

00:01:44.780 --> 00:01:47.410
JOANNA SMITH: So there's
a list of every bit of

00:01:47.410 --> 00:01:48.920
information that an
application is

00:01:48.920 --> 00:01:50.240
asking for the user.

00:01:50.240 --> 00:01:53.320
And they can actually control
not only which friends are

00:01:53.320 --> 00:01:56.020
going to see their app activity,
but which friends

00:01:56.020 --> 00:01:57.440
that app can see.

00:01:57.440 --> 00:02:00.400
So if a user decides to regulate
that, they can

00:02:00.400 --> 00:02:04.400
actually choose which circles
gets sent to that app.

00:02:04.400 --> 00:02:06.040
And maybe restrict it down.

00:02:06.040 --> 00:02:08.419
So maybe they have some people
in their circles that they

00:02:08.419 --> 00:02:10.810
don't necessarily want being
involved with them on this

00:02:10.810 --> 00:02:13.450
application, because it's
just not relevant.

00:02:13.450 --> 00:02:14.910
And they can control that.

00:02:14.910 --> 00:02:16.090
JONATHAN BERI: So I'm going to
remove my family circle, just

00:02:16.090 --> 00:02:17.840
because they don't take
really good pictures.

00:02:17.840 --> 00:02:19.850
JOANNA SMITH: Yeah,
they're terrible.

00:02:19.850 --> 00:02:21.310
And then we're going to--

00:02:21.310 --> 00:02:24.600
and then you can also control
which circles get to see any

00:02:24.600 --> 00:02:27.230
content generated by this
app, which is great.

00:02:27.230 --> 00:02:31.140
If you maybe don't necessarily
want to share photos with your

00:02:31.140 --> 00:02:33.840
sister, because she likes
to steal them all--

00:02:33.840 --> 00:02:35.430
so we'll go ahead and
take her out.

00:02:35.430 --> 00:02:37.420
JONATHAN BERI: And these are
called App Activities.

00:02:37.420 --> 00:02:38.870
JOANNA SMITH: And it also makes
it really easy for you

00:02:38.870 --> 00:02:40.900
to decide you don't want
to share anything.

00:02:40.900 --> 00:02:42.660
And you can go ahead at
the very top level

00:02:42.660 --> 00:02:44.160
and choose Only Me.

00:02:44.160 --> 00:02:46.030
And I think that's a really
powerful thing for the user.

00:02:46.030 --> 00:02:47.920
And it makes it really easy for
the developer, because you

00:02:47.920 --> 00:02:51.640
don't have to do anything
to allow this.

00:02:51.640 --> 00:02:54.190
JONATHAN BERI: And one great use
case for users-- and why

00:02:54.190 --> 00:02:56.200
we provide this as
a clear option--

00:02:56.200 --> 00:03:00.900
is if a particular application
is for your personal use.

00:03:00.900 --> 00:03:02.780
Maybe it's a fitness
application.

00:03:02.780 --> 00:03:04.510
And you may not want to share
all the activities you're

00:03:04.510 --> 00:03:07.020
doing within that fitness
application, but you do want

00:03:07.020 --> 00:03:07.940
that record.

00:03:07.940 --> 00:03:10.350
This is a great option for
those type of users.

00:03:10.350 --> 00:03:12.510
JOANNA SMITH: So it's really
great altogether.

00:03:12.510 --> 00:03:14.880
And then once they actually
authenticate, we have a really

00:03:14.880 --> 00:03:19.250
powerful option where if you
have an Android device, you

00:03:19.250 --> 00:03:22.530
can auto-install the application
on the user's

00:03:22.530 --> 00:03:25.260
Android phone just by
having them log in.

00:03:25.260 --> 00:03:27.480
JONATHAN BERI: And this
is from the website.

00:03:27.480 --> 00:03:29.010
We're not going to a
different store to

00:03:29.010 --> 00:03:30.270
initiate this process.

00:03:30.270 --> 00:03:32.620
This is from Photo Hunt's
application.

00:03:32.620 --> 00:03:34.070
JOANNA SMITH: It's the same pop
up that they're already

00:03:34.070 --> 00:03:35.340
seeing to continue
their login.

00:03:35.340 --> 00:03:38.130
And they can just choose right
now-- oh, yeah, I do want this

00:03:38.130 --> 00:03:38.670
on my phone.

00:03:38.670 --> 00:03:39.410
This is really simple.

00:03:39.410 --> 00:03:40.850
They don't have to search
through the Play store.

00:03:40.850 --> 00:03:42.520
They don't have to go through
any extra hoops.

00:03:42.520 --> 00:03:44.360
It's right there, and
it's really simple.

00:03:44.360 --> 00:03:46.510
So let's go ahead and add
it to our demo account.

00:03:46.510 --> 00:03:48.330
JONATHAN BERI: So I'm going
to hit install.

00:03:48.330 --> 00:03:49.710
It says it's downloading.

00:03:49.710 --> 00:03:51.100
JOANNA SMITH: So while that
downloads, we'll go ahead and

00:03:51.100 --> 00:03:53.440
look at the website.

00:03:53.440 --> 00:03:56.500
Now if you notice the demo
account is signed in-- it's

00:03:56.500 --> 00:03:57.130
personalized.

00:03:57.130 --> 00:03:59.120
We've got the profile picture.

00:03:59.120 --> 00:04:00.380
We've got their name.

00:04:00.380 --> 00:04:02.330
You can welcome them
to the site.

00:04:02.330 --> 00:04:03.930
And then you can also
show them their

00:04:03.930 --> 00:04:05.040
friends along the side.

00:04:05.040 --> 00:04:07.620
We have a list of friends
are also using this app.

00:04:07.620 --> 00:04:09.220
JONATHAN BERI: So this is
actually a new feature that

00:04:09.220 --> 00:04:11.690
we've introduced with
the sign-in button.

00:04:11.690 --> 00:04:12.910
JOANNA SMITH: Friend's list--

00:04:12.910 --> 00:04:14.580
the list of people in
a circle has not

00:04:14.580 --> 00:04:15.980
previously been available.

00:04:15.980 --> 00:04:18.180
It's important to note that
this is still a flat list.

00:04:18.180 --> 00:04:20.630
You cannot see the user's
actual circles.

00:04:20.630 --> 00:04:22.430
But you can see who they've
included in

00:04:22.430 --> 00:04:23.820
their social sphere.

00:04:23.820 --> 00:04:26.350
JONATHAN BERI: That's super
powerful to make social proof

00:04:26.350 --> 00:04:27.240
as part of your application.

00:04:27.240 --> 00:04:27.880
JOANNA SMITH: Definitely.

00:04:27.880 --> 00:04:31.600
And it can help you if you also
have support for a social

00:04:31.600 --> 00:04:32.910
graph within your
app natively.

00:04:32.910 --> 00:04:36.520
You can start using this to
connect users that already

00:04:36.520 --> 00:04:38.680
have accounts with you.

00:04:38.680 --> 00:04:39.860
So let's go ahead and
go to the phone.

00:04:39.860 --> 00:04:42.045
Is it still installing?

00:04:42.045 --> 00:04:43.780
JONATHAN BERI: I think
it may still be--

00:04:43.780 --> 00:04:45.140
JOANNA SMITH: Did we
get a notification?

00:04:45.140 --> 00:04:47.655
JONATHAN BERI: We didn't.

00:04:47.655 --> 00:04:49.610
JOANNA SMITH: Are we on Wi-Fi?

00:04:49.610 --> 00:04:51.790
JONATHAN BERI: We're on Wi-Fi.

00:04:51.790 --> 00:04:52.970
JOANNA SMITH: Well, let's go
ahead and talk about a

00:04:52.970 --> 00:04:54.090
different feature while
we wait for the

00:04:54.090 --> 00:04:56.210
internet to catch up.

00:04:56.210 --> 00:04:58.980
So the other thing that I'm
really excited about,

00:04:58.980 --> 00:05:02.200
personally, from this launch,
is the ability to use an

00:05:02.200 --> 00:05:03.910
interactive post.

00:05:03.910 --> 00:05:06.870
And this is very similar to
what we already have.

00:05:06.870 --> 00:05:08.760
It's a share that's
been expanded to

00:05:08.760 --> 00:05:10.300
have additional features.

00:05:10.300 --> 00:05:13.740
So now, in addition to that
normal share [INAUDIBLE], you

00:05:13.740 --> 00:05:16.530
might start seeing in your
stream a share with a button.

00:05:16.530 --> 00:05:18.840
And this button has a verb--
some sort of call to action.

00:05:18.840 --> 00:05:22.260
And that button can pull a user
from the Google+ stream

00:05:22.260 --> 00:05:23.880
into your application.

00:05:23.880 --> 00:05:25.420
JONATHAN BERI: So lets go ahead
and create one of these

00:05:25.420 --> 00:05:28.060
interactive posts.

00:05:28.060 --> 00:05:29.820
Right here, this is a
button, actually.

00:05:29.820 --> 00:05:30.880
It's part of the application--

00:05:30.880 --> 00:05:32.210
the Photo Hunt application.

00:05:32.210 --> 00:05:35.580
And there's a JavaScript API, so
you can scan it and make it

00:05:35.580 --> 00:05:37.220
integrated with your
application.

00:05:37.220 --> 00:05:40.360
So the user flow is nice.

00:05:40.360 --> 00:05:41.090
I did a vote.

00:05:41.090 --> 00:05:43.006
Which, in this case, I didn't do
an interactive post, but I

00:05:43.006 --> 00:05:44.075
can go ahead and promote it.

00:05:44.075 --> 00:05:46.520
So why don't you tell us
what's going on here?

00:05:46.520 --> 00:05:49.410
JOANNA SMITH: So at this, when
we're soliciting votes for our

00:05:49.410 --> 00:05:52.660
friends as well, because we
really like this photo, we are

00:05:52.660 --> 00:05:53.850
presented with a dialogue.

00:05:53.850 --> 00:05:56.400
And this dialogue-- like I
said, it's built off the

00:05:56.400 --> 00:05:57.490
existing share.

00:05:57.490 --> 00:06:00.000
But now we've got the
button that's there.

00:06:00.000 --> 00:06:01.960
And as a developer, you
can control that

00:06:01.960 --> 00:06:02.830
text on that button.

00:06:02.830 --> 00:06:04.030
You get to choose that string.

00:06:04.030 --> 00:06:06.570
And we have, I think,
over 100 right now.

00:06:06.570 --> 00:06:08.650
We have a lot of different
options, and we're taking more

00:06:08.650 --> 00:06:11.060
suggestions as we move along.

00:06:11.060 --> 00:06:13.230
The other thing that is
incredibly powerful is you can

00:06:13.230 --> 00:06:16.260
prefill the text in the
share dialogue.

00:06:16.260 --> 00:06:19.660
I think that's already been
done here with Photo Hunt.

00:06:19.660 --> 00:06:22.450
So you can get the user started
with maybe what you

00:06:22.450 --> 00:06:25.080
most want to promote from this
part of your application.

00:06:25.080 --> 00:06:28.430
You can also prefill up
to 10 recipients.

00:06:28.430 --> 00:06:32.340
So they won't be tagged in the
post, but they'll be directly

00:06:32.340 --> 00:06:32.930
shared with.

00:06:32.930 --> 00:06:35.575
So it will trigger a
notification on their end.

00:06:35.575 --> 00:06:39.270
JONATHAN BERI: And a powerful
part of including users

00:06:39.270 --> 00:06:40.310
already in the post.

00:06:40.310 --> 00:06:42.840
So prefilling recipients.

00:06:42.840 --> 00:06:46.040
Part of Google and Google+ is
our notification system.

00:06:46.040 --> 00:06:48.050
And when you explicitly mention
a user-- or sorry,

00:06:48.050 --> 00:06:49.730
include them in a share--

00:06:49.730 --> 00:06:52.600
we notify them across all
Google properties.

00:06:52.600 --> 00:06:54.710
So anywhere you see that little
red box, that will

00:06:54.710 --> 00:06:56.260
light up for those
particular users.

00:06:56.260 --> 00:06:59.920
Because the user who's allowing
this prefill has the

00:06:59.920 --> 00:07:01.350
intent to actually deliver
that message.

00:07:01.350 --> 00:07:03.110
So we have a guaranteed
delivery.

00:07:03.110 --> 00:07:06.370
And if those recipients also
have email configured for

00:07:06.370 --> 00:07:08.050
notifications, they'll get
an email if they're

00:07:08.050 --> 00:07:10.350
not by their desktop.

00:07:10.350 --> 00:07:13.250
And you can actually prefill
with email addresses.

00:07:13.250 --> 00:07:15.180
So if those users have a Google+
but maybe not using

00:07:15.180 --> 00:07:17.860
the app, or they haven't signed
up for Google+, yet

00:07:17.860 --> 00:07:21.220
they'll get that user flow and
can even upgrade which is

00:07:21.220 --> 00:07:23.430
pretty powerful to get more
users using your app.

00:07:23.430 --> 00:07:25.260
JOANNA SMITH: What's also
powerful is that if they are

00:07:25.260 --> 00:07:27.650
mentioned, or if the user
stumbles across your

00:07:27.650 --> 00:07:30.270
application's interactive person
that a different user

00:07:30.270 --> 00:07:32.630
has shared, when they click
on that, they may be

00:07:32.630 --> 00:07:33.820
taken to your app.

00:07:33.820 --> 00:07:35.670
But if they haven't already
signed up for your app,

00:07:35.670 --> 00:07:37.740
they'll be taken first to an
authentication screen so that

00:07:37.740 --> 00:07:38.800
they can sign up.

00:07:38.800 --> 00:07:42.190
And also they can install the
application onto their phone

00:07:42.190 --> 00:07:44.830
directly through the
identification screen, just

00:07:44.830 --> 00:07:45.650
like before.

00:07:45.650 --> 00:07:48.150
So there's a lot of different
entry points for a user to

00:07:48.150 --> 00:07:50.110
make their way into your
app from the Google+.

00:07:50.110 --> 00:07:53.010
JONATHAN BERI: So I'm going to
actually complete that share.

00:07:53.010 --> 00:07:56.476
And so now it should
be posting.

00:07:56.476 --> 00:07:58.010
JOANNA SMITH: I think we might
have forgotten to log into a

00:07:58.010 --> 00:08:00.340
second demo account, but we'll
just look at it on the stream

00:08:00.340 --> 00:08:01.010
of this one.

00:08:01.010 --> 00:08:01.360
JONATHAN BERI: Sure.

00:08:01.360 --> 00:08:02.610
Sure.

00:08:09.115 --> 00:08:10.090
There we go.

00:08:10.090 --> 00:08:12.690
This is the post we
just created.

00:08:12.690 --> 00:08:13.410
JOANNA SMITH: So you
can see, it's

00:08:13.410 --> 00:08:14.920
actually incredibly engaging.

00:08:14.920 --> 00:08:18.260
Because not only can users share
something that they care

00:08:18.260 --> 00:08:20.720
about with the people in their
circles, but now the people in

00:08:20.720 --> 00:08:22.600
their circles are involved
in that action.

00:08:22.600 --> 00:08:25.440
They can choose to go into the
app and create their own

00:08:25.440 --> 00:08:28.865
shares, or maybe they can do the
same action within the app

00:08:28.865 --> 00:08:30.160
and start interacting there.

00:08:30.160 --> 00:08:34.010
And so I think it's a really,
really engaging way to let

00:08:34.010 --> 00:08:37.100
your users interact.

00:08:37.100 --> 00:08:38.960
JONATHAN BERI: And ask their
friends to join them.

00:08:38.960 --> 00:08:41.159
That's the whole point of
an interactive post.

00:08:41.159 --> 00:08:44.520
It's about bringing your friends
who are across Google+

00:08:44.520 --> 00:08:46.490
into your app in a way
that they can start

00:08:46.490 --> 00:08:47.680
interacting with it.

00:08:47.680 --> 00:08:49.340
That's where the interactivity
comes from.

00:08:49.340 --> 00:08:52.310
And so we saw the preview
of the interactive post.

00:08:52.310 --> 00:08:54.200
And now this is what
users would see

00:08:54.200 --> 00:08:55.570
on the desktop stream.

00:08:55.570 --> 00:08:57.030
I'm going to click
on that post.

00:08:57.030 --> 00:08:59.830
And what's happening when
I click on that post?

00:08:59.830 --> 00:09:02.340
You see that I open
up the app.

00:09:02.340 --> 00:09:06.810
And what's unique about
this is the URL--

00:09:06.810 --> 00:09:08.700
that I was deep linked
back into the app.

00:09:08.700 --> 00:09:11.520
JOANNA SMITH: So we actually
enabled the deep link

00:09:11.520 --> 00:09:14.320
functionality last fall,
and a few of our clever

00:09:14.320 --> 00:09:15.660
developers caught it.

00:09:15.660 --> 00:09:17.680
But it's really, really
compelling.

00:09:17.680 --> 00:09:20.493
Because not only is a user taken
to your app, but they're

00:09:20.493 --> 00:09:23.440
taken into your app, to a
particular part-- a particular

00:09:23.440 --> 00:09:25.570
photo, or maybe particular
song.

00:09:25.570 --> 00:09:27.450
And that is the part that
they cared about.

00:09:27.450 --> 00:09:30.080
And so they get to skip the rest
and already be involved.

00:09:30.080 --> 00:09:33.420
And that's more likely to keep
a user in your app and grow

00:09:33.420 --> 00:09:34.900
your user base.

00:09:34.900 --> 00:09:36.830
JONATHAN BERI: And another
powerful thing about deep

00:09:36.830 --> 00:09:39.130
linking is support across
all platforms.

00:09:39.130 --> 00:09:41.290
So web, Android, iOS.

00:09:41.290 --> 00:09:43.680
So if a user is using an Android
application and they

00:09:43.680 --> 00:09:45.510
share it to their friends who
happen to be on a desktop, the

00:09:45.510 --> 00:09:47.900
deep link will take the user
to that desktop version.

00:09:47.900 --> 00:09:51.000
And now if another one of their
friends is on iOS, it

00:09:51.000 --> 00:09:53.770
will know and will take
them to be iOS app.

00:09:53.770 --> 00:09:54.910
JOANNA SMITH: And this is part
of the Google magic.

00:09:54.910 --> 00:09:58.750
You don't have to initiate the
support for these different

